SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1158
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Patrick Henry Mann, Jr.,
of Brownsville.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Patrick Henry Mann, Jr.; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Mann was a highly respected member of his community and a
consummate professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow
citizens in numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born on February 25, 1936, Mr. Mann was a lifelong resident of Haywood
County and a 1954 graduate of Haywood High School, where he was captain of the football
team; and
WHEREAS, Patrick Mann earned a bachelor's degree from Vanderbilt University and
graduated from Vanderbilt Law School in 1960, before returning to Brownsville to practice law,
embarking upon a career that spanned from 1961 to 2023; and
WHEREAS, a successful businessman, Patrick Mann had a passion for acquiring
farmland; he took an interest in the crops it yielded and the people who cultivated it, viewing the
land not merely as an investment but as a resource worthy of protection; and
WHEREAS, Patrick Mann was a devoted advisor and counselor to young men, including
farmers, lawyers, and fellow sportsmen, offering his time and wisdom and often reflecting on
time spent with his own mentor, Phil Williams, whom he deeply admired; and
WHEREAS, a true civic leader, Mr. Mann left an indelible mark on Brownsville, bringing
the Brownsville Amphitheater to life, refurbishing the memorial flame on the courthouse lawn,
commissioning murals around Courthouse Square, and installing the clock at Tamm Park; and
